                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12329608" author="djd" created="Sat, 17 Sep 2005 23:33:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not sure if it is an ASCII/EBCDIC problem as Derby/Java only uses UniCode at runtime.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12329844" author="myrna" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2005 22:28:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any other ideas as to what could cause a different id? The diff is like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(only showing value of first column - GLOBAL_XID - of the select in xa/xaOffline1, the rest is the same):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;GLOBAL_XID&lt;br/&gt;
expected:&lt;br/&gt;
  (1,776f6d626174,776f6d626174) &lt;br/&gt;
actual:&lt;br/&gt;
  (1,a696948281a3,a696948281a3)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12668698" author="kmarsden" created="Fri, 30 Jan 2009 01:24:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In xaHelper we have:&lt;br/&gt;
	private Xid makeXid(int xid)&lt;/p&gt;
	{
		return new ijXid(xid, databaseName.getBytes());
	}


&lt;p&gt;It should call getBytes with a consistent encoding so we don&apos;t get the diff.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12668948" author="kmarsden" created="Fri, 30 Jan 2009 17:39:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch for this issue. Ran xa tests on Windows and Z/OS.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
